  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to:\n\n1. Establish anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n2. Perform customer due diligence\n3. Report suspicious transactions to relevant authorities\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Screen customers against watch lists\n\nHowever, the specific details can vary by jurisdiction. I aim to provide general, factual information about legal compliance requirements.",
